Ilona Mask is forced to leave the post of Head of the board of Directors of Tesla
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and founder Tesla Alon Mask have settled their dispute over the fraud case.
This is reported by CNBC News.
According to the TV channel, the mask will have to leave the post of Head of the board of Directors of Tesla.
In this case, the Commission allowed the mask to retain the head of Tesla.
As noted, the founder of Tesla will also have to pay an administrative fine of $20 million.
A similar amount will be collected from Tesla.
The money will be distributed among the affected investors.
In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Ilona Mask-An American entrepreneur, who is on the list of 50 richest people planet according to Forbes magazine.
He is the head of the Space corporation SpaceX, the Neurotech company Neuralink and the developer of Tesla electric cars, as well as the co-founder of Paypal.
The Securities and Exchange Commission of the United States has previously sued the CEO of Tesla Ilona Maska for his tweet message about a possible redemption of the company.
Last month, Mask announced plans to make Tesla a private company and redeem all stock at the stock exchange at a fixed price of $420.
The value of the action in $420 was determined allegedly "because of the importance of this number in the culture of marijuana," the Bloomberg agency reported, citing the co-director of the Security Department of the Commission Stephen Peykin.
In this case, Ilona Mask subsequently refused his plans to redeem the shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman stated that he considers the accusations of fraud unfounded, and added that he is very disappointed and saddened by these claims.
"Honesty is the most important value in my life, and the facts will prove that I have no way of violating it," said the businessman in an interview with CNBC.
At the same time in August the group of shareholders Tesla filed against the mask a collective lawsuit, complaining about the financial losses suffered.
The plaintiffs claimed that the businessman's posts had brought them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that the businessman's tweets were misleading, because of which the sellers of Tesla shares were forced to buy the papers at artificially inflated prices to cover their positions.
Other plaintiffs also noted that the careless statements of Ilona Maska led to a sharp fluctuations of the course.
In September, Ilona Maska blamed the exchange frauds with the head of the research company Citron Research.
Meanwhile, if mask could not settle his dispute with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, he would be threatened with suspension from the management of the company and even prison.
This, in particular, was stated by users ' comments CNBC former chairman of the Commission Harvey Pitt.
Mask-"a good guy who can not manage the car company."
